      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY ULTIMATE BUDDHA (7) is a newcomer to the Josh Farrugia yard from Queensland where he has been tackling higher-graded races. Won the only time he raced here and draws for a trail so can measure up. RIO DE JANEIRO BLUE NZ (6) looks close to a win having come from a wider barrier for third at Menangle before drawing on the back row and making up plenty of ground for second at his latest appearance at this venue. If things go his way he could break through. GIMME A REASON (5) did a good job to come from wide on the back row and finish third last week, 2.6m behind Rio De Janeiro Blue. Returns to the front line so could turn the tables. OURTREACHEROUS REIGN NZ (8) has been racing well from this row including a last-start second and a win last month. Respect.",
